## Responsibilities

- Write unit, integration, and end-to-end tests
- Identify and close coverage gaps
- Refactor brittle tests into reliable ones
- Ensure test structure mirrors source structure in `{{TESTS_PATH}}`

## Before writing tests

1. Read `.github/copilot-instructions.md` for project-wide conventions
2. Survey existing tests in `{{TESTS_PATH}}` to understand testing patterns and utilities
3. Understand the code under test before writing assertions

## Testing principles

- Test behavior, not implementation details
- One assertion per logical concept; use descriptive test names
- Prefer real dependencies over mocks; mock only at system boundaries (network, database, time)
- Each test must be independent — no shared mutable state between tests

